Description: Fragment of neck and flattened, tapering handle to sharp turn of a RHodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '8'. Name Klenostratos. From a die close to that of Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, BIBALEX 0176.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (113)
